ure Animation\n* ''[[Thunderbirds (2004 film)|Thunderbirds]]'' (2004)\n* ''[[Troy (film)|Troy]]'' (2004)\n* ''[[Underdog (2007 film)|Underdog]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[Underworld (2003 film)|Underworld]]'' (2003)\n* ''[[V for Vendetta (film)|V for Vendetta]]'' (2005)\n* ''[[Walking with Beasts]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[Walking with Cavemen]]'' (2003)\n* ''[[Walking with Dinosaurs]]'' (1999)\n* ''[[Walking with Monsters]]'' (2005)\n* ''[[Wanted (2008 film)|Wanted]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[What Lies Beneath]]'' (2000)\n* ''[[Where the Wild Things Are (film)|Where the Wild Things Are]]'' (2009)\n* ''[[X-Men: The Last Stand]]'' (2006)\n\n==See also==\n* [[Weta Digital]]\n* [[Industrial Light & Magic]]\n*[[Moving Picture Company|Moving Picture Company (MPC)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.framestore.com}}\n* {{imdb company|0105094|The Computer Film Company}}\n*[https://www.wired.co.uk/article/the-image-engineers Wired article on the company]\n\n{{coord |51|30|54.2|N|0|8|11.7|W|type:landmark_region:GB-WSM|display=title}}\n\n{{Animation industry in the United Kingdom}}\n\n[[Category:Visual effects companies]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 2001]]\n[[Category:Best Visual Effects Academy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Computer animation]]\n[[Category:British animation studios]]\n[[Category:Special effects companies]]\n[[Category:Television and film post-production companies]]\n[[Category:Film production companies of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 1986]]\n[[Category:1986 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "Jamesmcmahon0", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's (2)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Framestore"}
{"title_page": "Sunday Best (Surfaces song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Sunday Best\n| type       = single\n| artist     = Surfaces\n| album      = Where the Light Is & Horizons\n| published  = January 8, 2019\n| released   = July 11, 2019 {{small|(music video)}}<br>March 2020 {{small|(airplay)}}\n| genre      =Pop\n| length     = 2:39\n| label      = {{hlist|TenThousand Projects|[[Caroline Records|Caroline]]}}\n| writer     = {{hlist|Forrest Frank|Colin Padalecki}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|Forrest Frank|Colin Padalecki}}\n| prev_title = Shine on Top\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = Palm Trees\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{external music video|type=single|{{YouTube|83KqwEEGw4|\"Sunday Best\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Sunday Best'''\" is a song by American [[electro-pop]] duo Surfaces, composed of Forrest Frank and Colin Padalecki. The song was released by TenThousand Projects and [[Caroline Records]] on the duo's second album ''Where the Light Is'' on January 8, 2019. The song was re-released as Surfaces' lead single off their third album ''Horizons'' on February 28, 2020''.'' The song's music video was released on July 11, 2019 and it shows the duo turning a boring office to a party place.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Surfaces-Shares-New-Music-Video-For-SUNDAY-BEST-20190711|title=Surfaces Shares New Music Video For SUNDAY BEST|date=July 11, 2019|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> The song is believed to have gained popularity in late February 2020 on the online-video sharing platform [[TikTok]] for its lyric \"Feeling good, like I should\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/branding/8551350/flighthouse-republic-records-partner-tiktok-series-certified-superfan|title=Flighthouse and Republic Records Partner on New TikTok Series 'Certified Superfan'|last=Eggertsen|first=Chris|date=February 19, 2020|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url-status=live|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> before it was released for radio airplay in early March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302133607/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|date=March 3, 2020|website=[[All Access]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302133607/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archive-date=March 2, 2020|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.top-charts.com/s/sunday-best-surfaces|title=Sunday Best by Surfaces|website=Top-Charts.com|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> The song peaked in the Top 40 in Australia, Canada, Norway, Ireland, New Zealand and the United Kingdom, as well as the top 100 in the United States, Switzerland, Germany and Sweden.\n\n== Live performances ==\nSurfaces made their late-night television debut when they performed the song on ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' on March 2, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2020/03/03/surfaces-perform-on-late-night-with-seth-meyers-first-look/|title=Surfaces Perform \"Sunday Best\" On \"Late Night With Seth Meyers\"|last=Cantor|first=Brian|date=March 3, 2020|website=Headline Planet|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n| 12\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|57|artist=Surfaces|song=Sunday Best|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 2, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|15|artist=Surfaces|song=Sunday Best|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia|39|artist=Surfaces|song=Sunday Best|r