itle19         = C\u00f3mo te atreves (acoustic)\n|note19          = \n|writer19        = \n|extra19         = \n|length19        = 3:51\n}}\n\n==References==\n\n[[Category:2016 albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Sobre el amor y sus efectos secundarios\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Morat (band)|Morat]]\n| cover      = Sobre el amor y sus efectos secundarios.jpg\n| released   = June 17, 2016\n| recorded   = 2014-2016\n| venue      =\n| studio     = \n| genre      = [[Latin pop]]\n| producer   = [[Universal Music Group]]\n| next_title = [[Balas perdidas]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n}}\n\n'''''Sobre El Amor Y Sus Efectos Secundarios''''' ({{trans|''Regarding Love and Its Side Effects''}}) is the first studio album by the Colombian band [[Morat (band)|Morat]]. The album was released on June 17, 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://radiosol.com/cd-de-la-semana-sobre-el-amor-y-sus-efectos-secundarios-de-morat|title=CD DE LA SEMANA: \u201cSOBRE EL AMOR Y SUS EFECTOS SECUNDARIOS\u201d DE MORAT|date=11 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Composition == \nJuan Pablo described this album as a story of songs connecting one after another \"that talk about different stages of love that any young person can go through, from the beginning of a relationship to the end, and the feeling of self-esteem of feeling good without that person\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/musica/20161004/41752187712/morat-paulina-rubio-entrevista.html|title=\u201cCedimos \u2018Mi nuevo vicio\u2019 a Paulina porque sab\u00edamos que har\u00edamos temas mejores\u201d|date=4 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Promotion ==\nOn November 29, 2016, Morat performed ''Sobre el amor y sus efectos secundarios'' in Bataplan Disco in [[San Sebasti\u00e1n]], Spain, with highlights on \"Mi nuevo vicio\" and \"C\u00f3mo te atreves\". This performance was organized by Cadena 100 as part of their 'Club 100' meetings. The invitations to attend this performance were sold out in the first day. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.diariovasco.com/planes/201611/29/morat-presenta-bataplan-album-20161129002236-v.html?ref=https:%2F%2Fwww.google.co.uk%2F|title=Morat presenta hoy en Batapl\u00e1n su \u00e1lbum 'Sobre el amor y sus efectos secundarios'|publisher=El Diario Vasco|date=29 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn March 9, 2017, Morat presented this album at a concert in Industrial Copera in [[Granada]], Spain.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.europapress.es/andalucia/noticia-morat-presentara-disco-amor-efectos-secundarios-marzo-granada-20170130125437.html|title=Morat presentar\u00e1 su disco 'Sobre el amor y sus efectos secundarios' el 9 de marzo en Granada|publisher=[[Europa Press]]|date=30 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\nThe single \"[[Mi Nuevo Vicio]]\" in collaboration with [[Paulina Rubio]] achieved great success, and peaked at No.4 on Billboard on June 6, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/morat/chart-history/MPE/song/879218|title=Chart History Morat \"Mi Nuevo Vicio\"}}</ref>The third single \"C\u00f3mo te atreves\" also peaked at No.6 on Billboard on February 18, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/morat/chart-history/MPE/song/1012582|title=Chart History Morat \"C\u00f3mo te atreves\"}}</ref> The song \"Aprender A Quererte\" is best known in Mexico as the theme song of the soap opera \"[[Hijas de la luna]]\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://virusmagazine.com.mx/2018/11/morat-nos-habla-del-amor-y-sus-efectos-secundarios/|title=Morat Nos Habla Del Amor Y Sus Efectos Secundarios|date=21 November 2018}}</ref> In addition, Morat obtained 4x Platinum Record as well as a Latin Grammy award nomination for \"C\u00f3mo te atreves\", and Golden Record for \"Cu\u00e1nto me duele\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.europapress.es/andalucia/noticia-morat-presentara-disco-amor-efectos-secundarios-marzo-granada-20170130125437.html|title=Morat presentar\u00e1 su disco 'Sobre el amor y sus efectos secundarios' el 9 de marzo en Granada|publisher=[[Europa Press]]|date=30 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn collaboration with [[\u00c1lvaro Soler]], the single \"Yo Contigo, T\u00fa Conmigo (The Gong Gong Song)\" was produced as the theme music of [[Despicable Me 3]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rlm.es/2017/06/12/morat-y-alvaro-soler-ponen-musica-a-gru-3-mi-villano-favorito-a-la-venta-el-16-de-junio/|title=MORAT Y \u00c1LVARO SOLER PONEN M\u00daSICA A \u2018GRU 3. MI VILLANO FAVORITO\u2019, A LA VENTA EL 16 DE JUNIO|date=12 June 2017}}</ref>, which was included in the re-issue of ''Sobre el amor y sus efectos secundarios''. The single peaked at No.9 on Billboard on August 19, 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/morat/chart-history/italy-digital-song-sales/song/1032342|title=Chart History Morat \"Yo Contigo, T\u00fa Conmigo\"}}</ref>, reached No.1 on radio in Spain<ref>{{cite news|url=https://national-report.com/besos-en-guerra-lanzamiento-de-morat-juanes/|title=MORAT & JUANES ESTRENAN \u201cBESOS EN GUERRA\u201d|publisher=National-Report}}</ref>, and won the \"Song of the Year\" award in [[LOS40 Music Awards 2017]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://los40.com/los40/2017/11/14/videos/1510672836_079372.html|title=\u2018YO CONTIGO, T\u00da CONMIGO\u2019 EN DIRECTO EN LOS40 MUSIC AWARDS|publisher=Los40}}</ref>.\n\n==Track Listing==\n\n{{Track Listing\n|collapsed       = \n|headline        = First Edition<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/sobre-el-amor-y-sus-efectos-secundarios-mw0002956624|title=Morat Sobre el Amor y Sus Efectos Secundarios|access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n|extra_column    = \n|total_length    = \n|writing_credits = yes \n|lyrics_credits  = \n|music_credits   = \n|title1          = [[Mi Nuevo Vicio|Mi nuevo vicio]]\n|note1           = \n|writer1         = \n|extra1          = \n|length1         = 3:57\n|title2          = En un solo d\u00eda\n|note2           = \n|writer2         = \n|extra2          = \n|length2         = 3:22\n|title3          = Aprender a quererte\n|