{main|FDGB-Pokal}}\n\n[[East Germany]] also had its own national cup: the [[FDGB Cup]], the cup of the  ''Freie Deutsche Gewerkschaftsbund'', the association of the East German trade unions. It was introduced in 1949 and awarded annually until 1991 after [[German reunification]] in 1990 led to the merger of the football leagues of the two Germanys.\n\n==Women's German Cup==\n{{main|DFB-Pokal Frauen}}\n\nSince 1981 women's football clubs have competed for the [[DFB-Pokal Frauen]]. An [[Women's football in the GDR#Cup|East German women's cup]] was also held from 1987 to 1991.\n\n==Media coverage==\n\n=== Austria, Germany, Liechtenstein, and Switzerland ===\nAt least one match per round is aired free on [[Das Erste]] (Germany only) and [[Sport1 (Germany)|Sport1]] respectively, total two matches per round. All matches are available on [[Sky Sport (Germany)|Sky Sport]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://go.dfb.de/watch-live|title=Where to watch - DFB|website=[[German Football Association|DFB]]|language=en|access-date=23 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/dfb-pokal/news-detail/pokalachtelfinale-zwei-bundesligakracher-im-free-tv-195222/?no_cache=1&cHash=4d4aa2cde06db548593b824fc7c0f00a|title=Pokalachtelfinale: Zwei Bundesligakracher im Free-TV |website=[[German Football Association|DFB]]|language=de | date = 24 April 2019 |access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref> In Austria, one match per round also aired free on [[ServusTV]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.servus.com/tv/dfb-pokal-energie-cottbus-vs-fc-bayern-muenchen-bei-servustv-und-im-livestream/|title=DFB-Pokal: Energie Cottbus vs. FC Bayern M\u00fcnchen bei ServusTV und im Livestream|date=9 August 2019|website=Servus TV|language=de-DE|access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== International ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Country\n!Broadcaster\n!Ref\n|-\n|Unsold markets (exclude Indonesia)\n|[[YouTube]]\n|\n|-\n|Albania\n|[[RTSH]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B0stUArAX8w/|title=Radio Televi